Description:
The E-commerce Operations Officer is accountable for processing purchases and sales orders on a daily basis including the placement and tracking of orders, management of shipments, and order fulfillment.Main Duties And ResponsibilitiesProcess customer orders for all products in compliance with the company's policies and procedures;
Receive, review, acknowledge, and place customer sales orders accurately and promptly on the ERP system;
Fulfill orders once released from credit;
Track shipments and update internal stakeholders on order backlogs and information;
Work with logistics, sales, and credit teams to ensure order fulfillment in a timely manner;
Handle customer complaints in a timely manner and escalate issues when necessary;
Investigate product complaints and raise Return Material Authorization (RMA) requests with Vendors;
Invoice software, services, and licenses to customers following credit approval.
Receive stock and assure its valid.
Manage in-bound and out-bound shipments and assure accurate inventory.Skills
